#problem 15 : Write a program to read two lines of input and print the word after removing the character at the given index.

w = input("enter a string : ")
i = int(input("enter the index to be removed: "))

cond = len(w)-1  #condition to check whether the length of string is equal or greater than the given index

if (i >= cond):
    print(w)
else:              # else the given index will be removed, and print the string.
    first = w[0:i]
    last = w[i+1: ]

    print(first+last)

# sample test cases 
[1] enter a string : completeness
    enter the index : 12
    completeness
[2] enter a string : querty
    enter the index : 2
    qurty
